  "rationale": "<p>The correct answer is \u22121/12. Write the roots as fractional exponents: \u221c(x\u2075) = x^(5/4) and \u221b(x\u2074) = x^(4/3). So x^(5/4) / x^(4/3) = x^(5/4 \u2212 4/3) = x^(15/12 \u2212 16/12) = x^(\u22121/12). Therefore a/b = \u22121/12 \u2248 \u22120.0833.</p>",
